@startuml
!pragma teoz true
!pragma sequenceMessageSpan true
title Event Dispatch Cycle & Ordering Model (Deterministic + Fail-Fast)
hide footbox
autonumber "<color:#8fb6ff><b>[000]</b></color> "
skinparam maxMessageSize 48
skinparam ParticipantPadding 24
skinparam BoxPadding 12
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

' =========================
' DARK MODE REVIEW THEME
' =========================

skinparam backgroundColor #121417
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName JetBrains Mono
skinparam defaultFontColor #f3f5f7

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #79b8ff
  ArrowFontColor #f3f5f7

  LifeLineBorderColor #6d7986
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #1f262d

  ParticipantBorderColor #738396
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #25303a
  ParticipantFontColor #ffffff

  ActorBorderColor #98a7b8
  ActorBackgroundColor #2b3742
  ActorFontColor #ffffff

  GroupBorderColor #5f6a75
  GroupBackgroundColor #1a2128
  GroupFontColor #ffffff

  DividerBorderColor #5f6a75
  DividerBackgroundColor #1f262d
  DividerFontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #2a3138
  BorderColor #8b98a6
  FontColor #f3f5f7
}

box "Runtime Domain" #22352b
control "Core Tick Loop" as TickLoop
control "Event Router" as Router
control "Locked Topology\n+ Ordering Table" as Topology
end box

box "Mod/Capability Domain" #31283b
participant "Provider Sim\n(Mod A)" as ProviderSim
participant "Provider Audio\n(Mod B)" as ProviderAudio
participant "Consumer Render\n(Mod X)" as ConsumerRender
participant "Consumer UI\n(Mod Y)" as ConsumerUI
end box

== Boot-Lock Prerequisite ==

TickLoop -> Topology: Load immutable channel topology
Topology --> TickLoop: Channel modes + publisher rights + subscriber order

== Tick N Dispatch ==

ProviderSim -> Router: Publish SimTick event\n(channel=broadcast.sim_tick)
ProviderAudio -> Router: Publish AudioCommandRequested\n(channel=queue.audio_cmd)

Router -> Topology: Validate publisher rights + channel mode
Topology --> Router: valid

group Deterministic broadcast delivery
TickLoop -> Router: Dispatch channel=broadcast.sim_tick
Router -> ConsumerRender: Handle SimTick (ordered)
Router -> ConsumerUI: Handle SimTick (ordered)
end

group Directed request/response
ConsumerRender -> Router: Query DamagePreview(req)\n(channel=direct.damage_query)
Router -> Topology: Resolve unique owner for direct.damage_query
Topology --> Router: owner = ProviderSim
Router -> ProviderSim: Forward DamagePreview(req)
ProviderSim --> Router: DamagePreview(resp)
Router --> ConsumerRender: DamagePreview(resp)
end

group Deterministic queue drain point
TickLoop -> Router: Drain queue.audio_cmd\n(phase boundary)
Router -> ProviderAudio: Deliver queued command(s)\n(FIFO within deterministic global order)
end

alt Unauthorized publisher OR owner ambiguity detected
  Router -> TickLoop: Hard-fail runtime\n(invariant violation safety net)
else No violation
  Router --> TickLoop: Tick dispatch completed
end

note across
Dispatch invariants:
- Channel topology and rights are locked before ticks start
- Subscriber order is deterministic (derived from locked load order)
- Exclusive-owner channel ambiguity is rejected
- Runtime keeps hard-fail safety net even after admission checks
end note

@enduml
